19/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The presidency adopted a document Wednesday (18 June) presenting the country's stance on EU enlargement. 
It will serve as a guideline for the BiH delegation attending the EU Summit in Thessaloniki, Greece. 
Delegates are expected to present a report at the forum on Saturday.
In other news, police in Republika Srpska arrested nine people on Wednesday in connection with arms smuggling. 
Officials say the ring supplied weapons to an Islamic organisation, the Brotherhood of Young Muslims. 
(Dnevni List, Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 19/06/03; Onasa, FoNet, BBC - 18/06/03)
